The paper deals with automated real-time prediction of ergonomic risks of manipulating objects using RGB-D camera videos. This involves learning spatial features using deep convolutional models and segmenting frames into a hierarchy of actions using temporal convolutional networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also deals with human-robot collaboration systems for logistics and manufacturing applications, which falls under the sub-category cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also focuses on ergonomics, which is a sub-field of human-computer interaction (HCI), and hence, cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is another likely sub-category. The use of deep learning models for segmentation and classification also suggests the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
